for (j in lev) {
  for (i in 1:dim(data_test)[1]) {
    if (j==lev[1]) {
      eta_clmm_t.0[i,j]=as.numeric(clmm.0$Theta[which(lev==j)]) - ifelse(data_test$regular[i]==0, clmm.0$beta[1], ifelse(data_test$regular[i]==1,clmm.0$beta[2],0)) - ifelse(data_test$nationality[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[3], 0) - ifelse(data_test$gender[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[4], 0) - ifelse(data_test$PDP[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[5], 0) - data_test$tenured_teachers[i] * clmm.0$beta[6] - data_test$absence[i] * clmm.0$beta[7] - data_test$merit_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[8] - data_test$disciplinary_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[9] - data_test$commitment_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[10] - data_test$delays[i] * clmm.0$beta[11] - clmm.0$ranef[data_test$group[i]]
      mu_clmm_t.0[i,j]=plogis(eta_clmm_t.0[i,j])
    } else if(j==lev[length(lev)]) {
      eta_clmm_t.0[i,j]=qlogis(0.999)
      mu_clmm_t.0[i,j]=1 - plogis(as.numeric(clmm.0$Theta[which(lev==j)-1]) - ifelse(data_test$regular[i]==0, clmm.0$beta[1], ifelse(data_test$regular[i]==1,clmm.0$beta[2],0)) - ifelse(data_test$nationality[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[3], 0) - ifelse(data_test$gender[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[4], 0) - ifelse(data_test$PDP[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[5], 0) - data_test$tenured_teachers[i] * clmm.0$beta[6] - data_test$absence[i] * clmm.0$beta[7] - data_test$merit_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[8] - data_test$disciplinary_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[9] - data_test$commitment_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[10] - data_test$delays[i] * clmm.0$beta[11] - clmm.0$ranef[data_test$group[i]])
    } else {
      eta_clmm_t.0[i,j]=as.numeric(clmm.0$Theta[which(lev==j)]) - ifelse(data_test$regular[i]==0, clmm.0$beta[1], ifelse(data_test$regular[i]==1,clmm.0$beta[2],0)) - ifelse(data_test$nationality[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[3], 0) - ifelse(data_test$gender[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[4], 0) - ifelse(data_test$PDP[i]==1, clmm.0$beta[5], 0) - data_test$tenured_teachers[i] * clmm.0$beta[6] - data_test$absence[i] * clmm.0$beta[7] - data_test$merit_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[8] - data_test$disciplinary_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[9] - data_test$commitment_notes[i] * clmm.0$beta[10] - data_test$delays[i] * clmm.0$beta[11] - clmm.0$ranef[data_test$group[i]]

PARTIAL PLOT - ordinal forest

var.names_cat=c("regular","nationality","gender","PDP")
var.names_cont0=c("tenured_teachers","absence","merit_notes","disciplinary_notes","commitment_notes","delays")
var.names_cont1=c("tenured_teachers","first_term_math","absence","merit_notes","disciplinary_notes","commitment_notes","delays","variance")
var.names_cont2=c("tenured_teachers","first_term_math","absence","merit_notes","disciplinary_notes","commitment_notes","delays","variance","previous_math")

for (i in 1:length(var.names_cat)) {
    xv <- forest.data[,var.names_cat[i]]
    x.pt <- levels(xv)
    y.pt <- numeric(length(x.pt))
    n <- nrow(forest.data) 
    ylab <- c("p(x=4)","p(x=5)","p(x=6)","p(x=7)","p(x=8)","p(x=9)","p(x=10)")
    par(mfrow=c(2,4))
    for (j in 4:10) {
      for (k in seq(along = x.pt)) {
        focus <- j-3 #class (of y)
        x.data <- forest.data
        x.data[, var.names_cat[i]] <- factor(rep(x.pt[k], n), levels = x.pt)
        pr <- predict(ordforest.0, x.data, type = "prob")$classprobs
        y.pt[k] <- mean(pr[, focus])
      }
      barplot(y.pt, width=rep(1, length(y.pt)), col="blue",
              xlab = var.names_cat[i], ylab = ylab[j-3], names.arg=x.pt)
    }
}
